h5mgm is a tool to convert the HDF5 files written by LUMA into a set of VTK files to be read by Paraview.
Parameters are passed as a single command line argument as follows:
	h5mgm <arg>

Valid options for the argument are:

	quiet		Silences warnings of missing datasets. Useful if you write non-conforming HDF5 files using something other than LUMA.
	XXX			Where XXX are three numbers to be appended to the VTK filename to differntiate cases. e.g. h5mgm 000 will produce files named something like "vtk.000.t.vtk"
	version		Prints the version number of the tool compiled on your system.
	loud		Prints out the mesh building progress.